galaxis
------------------------------------------
This is a UNIX-hosted, curses-based clone of the nifty little Macintosh
freeware game Galaxis.

Lifeboats from a crippled interstellar liner are adrift in a starfield.
To find them, you can place probes that look in all eight compass
directions and tell you how many lifeboats they see.  Your objective:
find the lifeboats as quickly as possible, before the stranded
passengers run out of oxygen!

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-15
  libncurses8-5.5-3

Build requirements:
  binutils-20080624-2
  cygport-0.4.0-1
  gcc-3.4.4-3
  make-3.81-1

Canonical homepage:
  http://www.catb.org/~esr/galaxis/

------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack galaxis-1.7-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./galaxis-1.7-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/galaxis-1.7-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/galaxis-1.7-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/bin/galaxis.exe
  /usr/share/doc/galaxis-1.7/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/galaxis-1.7/README
  /usr/share/man/man6/galaxis.6.gz

------------------

